Class PathProfiler

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.scijava.AbstractContextual
      • org.scijava.command.ContextCommand
        • sc.fiji.snt.analysis.PathProfiler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable, org.scijava.Cancelable, org.scijava.command.Command, org.scijava.Contextual, org.scijava.plugin.SciJavaPlugin

    public class PathProfiler
extends org.scijava.command.ContextCommand
    Command to retrieve Profile plots (plots of voxel intensities values along a Path) from reconstructions.
    Author:
    Tiago Ferreira

    • Constructor Detail

      • PathProfiler

        public PathProfiler(Tree tree,
                    ij.ImagePlus imp)
        Instantiates a new Profiler
        Parameters:
        tree - the Tree to be profiled
        imp - the image from which pixel intensities will be retrieved. Note that no effort is made to ensure that the image is suitable for profiling, if Tree nodes lay outside the image dimensions, pixels intensities will be retrieved as Float#NaN

      • PathProfiler

                    ij.ImagePlus imp)
        Instantiates a new Profiler from a single path
        Parameters:
        path - the path to be profiled
        imp - the image from which pixel intensities will be retrieved. Note that no effort is made to ensure that the image is suitable for profiling, if Tree nodes lay outside the image dimensions, pixels intensities will be retrieved as Float#NaN

        public boolean validImage()
        Checks whether the specified image contains all the nodes of the profiled Tree/Path.
        Returns:
        true, if successful, false if Tree has nodes outside the image boundaries.

      • setNodeIndicesAsDistances

        public void setNodeIndicesAsDistances(boolean nodeIndices)
        Sets whether the profile abscissae should be reported in real-word units (the default) or node indices (zero-based). Must be called before calling getValues(Path), getPlot() or getXYPlot().
        Parameters:
        nodeIndices - If true, distances will be reported as indices.

      • getValues

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.List<java.lang.Double>> getValues(Path p)
        Gets the profile for the specified path as a map of lists, with distances (or indices) stored under X_VALUES ("x-values") and intensities under Y_VALUES ("y-values").
        Parameters:
        p - the path to be profiled
        Returns:
        the profile
